relevant_findings.HEENT: Anicteric sclera, pink conjunctiva, patent nares, dry mucous membranes, poor dentition
relevant_findings.neck: Nontender, supple, no lymphadenopathy (LAD), no jugular venous distention (JVD)
relevant_findings.cardiac: Regular, slightly tachycardic (rate not specified), normal S1/S2, no murmurs, gallops, or rubs
relevant_findings.lung: Clear to auscultation bilaterally (CTAB), no wheezes, rales, or rhonchi
relevant_findings.abdomen: Soft, tender to palpation (TTP) in epigastric and periumbilical regions, slightly distended, hyperactive bowel sounds, no rebound or guarding, no hepatosplenomegaly
relevant_findings.extremities: Moving all extremities well, no cyanosis, clubbing, or edema
relevant_findings.neurological: Cranial nerves II-XII grossly intact, acutely intoxicated with poor attention, unwilling to further participate, no asterixis
relevant_findings.skin: Warm and well perfused, no excoriations, lesions, or rashes
